    "plan_content": "## Plan: Add `next/geo` Geolocation Utility Module\n\nAfter studying `server.js`, `server.d.ts`, and `user-agent.ts`, here's the exact approach:\n\n---\n\n### Files to Create (4 new) + Modify (1)\n\n| File | Action |\n|---|---|\n| `packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/geo.ts` | New — core implementation |\n| `packages/next/geo.js` | New — CommonJS public entry point |\n| `packages/next/geo.d.ts` | New — TypeScript type definitions |\n| `packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/geo.test.ts` | New — unit tests |\n| `packages/next/package.json` | Modify — add `geo.js`/`geo.d.ts` to `files` array |\n\n---\n\n### Step 1 — `geo.ts` (core implementation)\n\nPure TypeScript, no external imports. Key design decisions:\n- `headers.get()` returns `null` when absent; use `?? undefined` to convert `null` → `undefined` for strict TypeScript optional fields\n- `cf-ipcountry` (Cloudflare) is a fallback: `headers.get('x-vercel-ip-country') ?? headers.get('cf-ipcountry') ?? undefined` — Vercel header wins if present\n- `country` is derived from `countryCode` via a `COUNTRY_NAMES` map (10 entries: US, GB, DE, FR, JP, CN, IN, BR, AU, CA); returns `undefined` if code not in map\n- `isInRegion` normalizes both sides with `.toUpperCase()` for case-insensitive comparison\n- `geoDistance` uses the standard Haversine formula with R = 6371 km\n\n### Step 2 — `geo.js` (entry point)\n\nExact mirror of `server.js`: object literal + repeated `exports.X =` assignments for both CJS and named-import compatibility.\n\n### Step 3 — `geo.d.ts` (types)\n\nExact mirror of `server.d.ts`: `export type { Geo }` + `export { geo, geoFromHeaders, isInRegion, geoDistance }` all from `'next/dist/server/web/spec-extension/geo'`.\n\n### Step 4 — `package.json` `files` array\n\nInsert `\"geo.js\"` and `\"geo.d.ts\"` after `\"form.d.ts\"` (line 43) — `g` follows `f` alphabetically.\n\n### Step 5 — `geo.test.ts` (12 test cases)\n\nUses Jest globals (`describe`/`it`/`expect`) without explicit imports, matching the pattern of the existing co-located adapter tests. Covers:\n- `geo()` with all Vercel headers present → all fields populated including `country: 'United States'`\n- `geo()` with no headers → all fields `undefined`\n- `geoFromHeaders()` with Cloudflare-only headers → `countryCode` from `cf-ipcountry`\n- Vercel header wins when both Vercel + Cloudflare present\n- `isInRegion()`: match, no-match, case-insensitive, missing `countryCode`\n- `geoDistance()`: NY→London ≈ 5,570 km (±50 km tolerance)\n- Country name lookup: `GB` → `'United Kingdom'`, unknown code → `undefined`\n\n### Verification\n\n```bash\npnpm --filter=next types       # type-check (~10s)\npnpm test-unit packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/geo.test.ts\npnpm --filter=next build       # ensure dist/ output resolves correctly\n```",
